Here is the breakdown of how they work together in your project:

1.
Delta Lake (The "How")
Delta Lake is the storage technology (the engine). It is a layer that sits on top of your Parquet files to make them act like a real database.

ACID Transactions:
It ensures that if a streaming micro-batch fails halfway through, nothing is written (no partial/corrupted data).
Time Travel:
You can "go back in time" to see what the data looked like 10 minutes ago.
Schema Enforcement: 
It prevents "junk" data with the wrong columns from breaking your tables.
Analogy:
Delta is the Warehouse Building itself. It provides the security, the logs, and the structure.

